



Sir
In Council April 2d 1781



The General Assembly having directed that no Money should be paid for Horses till their Meeting in the ensuing Month puts it out of the power of the Executive to honour General Greenes Draughts for those purposes on Demand. I am very sorry that this Measure [324] should be likely to involve the Honble. the Delegates of Georgia in Inconveniencies, which it is out of our power to prevent. I am

T. J.

